1.20	Chamkila	Amar Singh Chamkila	Amar Singh Chamkila (Punjabi: ) (July 21, 1960 â€“ March 8, 1988) was a controversial Punjabi singer, songwriter, and musician. His detractors lamented the vulgarity in his songs while his fans relished their sensual appeal. He was also among the major Punjabi live stage performers or Akhara singers. In his heyday, he was known to do three stage performances in a single day.	
